227.8	The_Emperor's_New_Clothes	The Emperor's New Clothes	"The Emperor's New Clothes" (Danish: ) is a short tale by Hans Christian Andersen about two weavers who promise an Emperor a new suit of clothes that is invisible to those unfit for their positions, stupid, or incompetent. When the Emperor parades before his subjects in his new clothes, a child cries out, "But he isn't wearing anything at all!" The tale has been translated into over a hundred languages.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Emperor_Clothes_01.jpg/220px-Emperor_Clothes_01.jpg
